post.summary: Enter parameters, keywords, or a manufacturer part number/DigiKey part number and receive limited product information for each match. Note that MyPricing is not returned.
post.description:
Search for product information based on part number, description, manufacturer, or category. This new API supports two-legged and three-legged OAuth authentication. 
[all endpoints for https://developer.digikey.com/products/product-information-v4/productsearch]

MyPricing is not available in the KeywordSearch response, and only StandardPricing is returned.
Please use the ProductDetails or ProductPricing endpoints to receive MyPricing

parameters.name: X-DIGIKEY-Client-Id
parameters.description: The Client Id for your app.

parameters.name: X-DIGIKEY-Locale-Language
parameters.description:
Two letter code for language to search on. Langauge must be supported by the selected site. If searching on keyword, this language is used to find matches. Acceptable values include: en, ja, de, fr, ko, zhs, zht, it, es, he, nl, sv, pl, fi, da, no.
Default value: en

parameters.name: X-DIGIKEY-Locale-Currency
parameters.description:
Three letter code for Currency to return part pricing for. Currency must be supported by the selected site. Acceptable values include: USD, CAD, JPY, GBP, EUR, HKD, SGD, TWD, KRW, AUD, NZD, INR, DKK, NOK, SEK, ILS, CNY, PLN, CHF, CZK, HUF, RON, ZAR, MYR, THB, PHP.
Default value: primary currency for the entered Locale-site.

parameters.name: X-DIGIKEY-Locale-Site
parameters.description:
Two letter code for Digi-Key product website to search on. Different countries sites have different part restrictions, supported languages, and currencies. Acceptable values include: US, CA, JP, UK, DE, AT, BE, DK, FI, GR, IE, IT, LU, NL, NO, PT, ES, KR, HK, SG, CN, TW, AU, FR, IN, NZ, SE, MX, CH, IL, PL, SK, SI, LV, LT, EE, CZ, HU, BG, MY, ZA, RO, TH, PH.
Default value: US

parameters.name: X-DIGIKEY-Customer-Id
parameters.description: This value determines if MyPricing, if available, will be returned and which region’s pricing agreement will be used. MyPricing is set for the country of the CustomerID’s physical location. The CustomerID must have a myDIGIKEY registration tied to that location.

get.description:

get.summary: Enter a manufacturer part number/DigiKey part number or partial manufacturer part number/DigiKey part number and receive product information for each matched product. MyPricing is shown if applicable.
get.description: Allows you to use inStock and excludeMarketplace as limit. If there are multiple matching parts, you can see the additional ones by incrementing your input using the offset and limit fields. Locale information is required in the headers for accurate pricing and currencies. Locale and currencies will be set to default values if not populated or populated with invalid values. Check the “Settings Used” fields to see which values we used for the response.

parameters.name: productNumber
parameters.description: ProductNumber to search on. Can be partial part number, manufacturer part number, or a Digi-Key part number.	Enter the ProductNumber to be searched. You can enter a manufacturer part number or a DigiKey part number. You can enter a partial or complete product number. The search results are better when entering a DigiKey product number, as some manufacturers share the same manufacturer part number.

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: Enter the maximum number of products to be returned. The maximum amount is 10. Default value: 5

parameters.name: offset
parameters.description: Enter the starting index for the records to be returned. This is used when making subsequent calls for the same ProductNumber. Default value: 0

parameters.name: inStock
parameters.description: Enter true to exclude products that are not in stock. Default value : false

parameters.name: excludeMarketplace
parameters.description: Enter true to exclude Marketplace items and limit results to those fulfilled by DigiKey. Default value: false

parameters.name: X-DIGIKEY-Locale-Site
parameters.description:
This value determines which country’s prices are used for StandardPricing and MyPricing. Also, product restrictions can differ by country. Acceptable values include: AT, AU, BE, BG, BR, CA, CH, CN, CZ, DE, DK, EE, ES, FI, FR, GR, HK, HU, IE, IL, IN, IT, JP, KR, LT, LU, LV, MX, MY, NL, NO, NZ, PH, PL, PT, RO, SE, SG, SI, SK, TH, TW, UK, US, ZA
Default value: US

parameters.name: X-DIGIKEY-Locale-Language
parameters.description:
This value determines which language is used for the links in reply. If the entered language is not valid for the entered Locale-Site, it will default to English. Acceptable values include: CS, DA, DE, EN, ES, FI, FR, HE, HU, IT, JA, KO, NL, NO, PL, PT, RO, SV, TH, ZHS, ZHT
Default value: English

parameters.name: X-DIGIKEY-Locale-Currency
parameters.description:
This value determines which country’s prices are used for StandardPricing and MyPricing. If the value is not allowed for the entered Locale-Site, it defaults to the primary currency for that Locale-Site. Ex: If Locale-Currency = EUR and Locale-Site = US, then the system will default to USD and note that in the response. Acceptable values include: AUD, CAD, CHF, CNY, CZK, DKK, EUR, GBP, HKD, HUF, ILS, INR, JPY, KRW, MYR, NOK, NZD, PHP, PLN, RON, SEK, SGD, THB, TWD, USD, ZAR
Default value: primary currency for the entered Locale-site.

parameters.name: X-DIGIKEY-Customer-Id
parameters.description: This value determines if MyPricing, if available, will be returned and which region’s pricing agreement will be used. MyPricing is set for the country of the CustomerID’s physical location. The CustomerID must have a myDIGIKEY registration tied to that location.

parameters.name: X-DIGIKEY-Client-Id
parameters.description: The Client Id for your App. Enter the ClientID for the Product App used to make the call.

get.summary: Enter a manufacturer part number/DigiKey part number and requested quantity to receive the price for that quantity. MyPricing is shown if applicable.
get.description:
The PricingOption in the response may contain up to four sets of pricing.
  • Exact: We priced the exact amount you requested.
  • MinimumOrderQuantity: We increased the amount you requested to the minimum order quantity
  • MaxOrderQuantity : We lowered the amount you requested to the maximum order quantity
  • BetterValue: We increased the amount you requested to match a manufacturer's standard package and the total cost is lower than the amount you requested.

parameters.name: productNumber
parameters.description: ProductNumber to search on. You can enter a manufacturer part number or a DigiKey part number. The search results are better when entering a DigiKey product number, as some manufacturers share the same manufacturer part number.

parameters.name: requestedQuantity
parameters.description: The RequestedQuantity we used for the API call.

parameters.name: manufacturerId
parameters.description: Use when searching for manufacturer product numbers like CR2032 that will match with multiple manufacturers. Setting this query field to a manufacturer id will get the exact match you want. You can look up the manufacturer id in the Manufacturers endpoint.

parameters.name: X-DIGIKEY-Client-Id
parameters.description: The Client Id for your app.

parameters.name: X-DIGIKEY-Locale-Language
parameters.description:
Two letter code for language to search on. Langauge must be supported by the selected site. If searching on keyword, this language is used to find matches. Acceptable values include: en, ja, de, fr, ko, zhs, zht, it, es, he, nl, sv, pl, fi, da, no.
Default value: en

parameters.name: X-DIGIKEY-Locale-Currency
parameters.description:
Three letter code for Currency to return part pricing for. Currency must be supported by the selected site. Acceptable values include: USD, CAD, JPY, GBP, EUR, HKD, SGD, TWD, KRW, AUD, NZD, INR, DKK, NOK, SEK, ILS, CNY, PLN, CHF, CZK, HUF, RON, ZAR, MYR, THB, PHP.
Default value: primary currency for the entered Locale-site.

parameters.name: X-DIGIKEY-Locale-Site
parameters.description:
Two letter code for Digi-Key product website to search on. Different countries sites have different part restrictions, supported languages, and currencies. Acceptable values include: US, CA, JP, UK, DE, AT, BE, DK, FI, GR, IE, IT, LU, NL, NO, PT, ES, KR, HK, SG, CN, TW, AU, FR, IN, NZ, SE, MX, CH, IL, PL, SK, SI, LV, LT, EE, CZ, HU, BG, MY, ZA, RO, TH, PH.
Default value: US

parameters.name: X-DIGIKEY-Customer-Id
parameters.description: Your Digi-Key Customer id. If your account has multiple Customer Ids for different regions, this allows you to select one of them.
